Wash and dry all produce. Halve, core, and finely dice @green bell pepper{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Drain and rinse @kidney beans{13.4%ounce}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook until lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in scallion whites and half the garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @celery salt{1%tsp}, and @blackening spice{1%tbsp}. Cook until thoroughly coated, ~{30%seconds} more.

Add beans to pot with aromatics; cook, stirring, until combined. Add @veggie stock concentrate{3} and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> If stewed beans are too thick, add another splash of water.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of vegetable oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in kale, @water{1/4%cup}, and remaining @veggie stock concentrates{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has evaporated and kale is wilted and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, stewed beans, and kale between #bowls{}. Dollop beans with @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Drizzle with @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.